<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About Eugene Choi"
	pubDate={new Date('April 16 2026')}
>
	<p>
		I'm a data engineer. I currently lead data infrastructure at a small real-estate-sourcing company — address
		normalization at ~200M records, identity design across Elasticsearch and Postgres, and the kind of migration work
		where the wrong call costs you six months.
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog is where I work through the harder architecture decisions in public. I write to sharpen my own thinking
		and to invite feedback from people who've solved similar problems at different scales.
	</p>

	<p>
		You can find me on <a href="https://github.com/eugeneiohc">GitHub</a>. If you want to talk shop, email me at
		eugeneiohc [at] gmail [dot] com.
	</p>
</Layout>
